OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FGeetanjali Shree is first  
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25FIndian winner of           
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5FInternational Booker Prize 
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Geetanjali Shree has become the first  
OL,6, Indian writer to win the International 
OL,7, Booker Prize.                          
OL,9,FHer novel Tomb of Sand, a family saga  
OL,10,Fset in the shadow of the partition of  
OL,11,FIndia, follows an 80-year-old woman    
OL,12,Fafter the death of her husband.        
OL,14,FIt was the first Hindi-language book to
OL,15,Fbe shortlisted for the #50,000 prize.  
OL,17,F"I never dreamt of the Booker, I never 
OL,18,Fthought I could," Ms Shree said. "What 
OL,19,Fa huge recognition. I'm amazed,        
OL,20,Fdelighted, honoured and humbled."      
